variables.text: Grabs can be canceled instantly by pressing the opposite direction of where you're going. This technique is refered to as a mach cancel and is used to stop Peppino from running without skidding, or to turn around without needing to drift. In the following section, try inputting a grab and press the opposite direction before hitting the teleporters.

After performing a mach cancel you can immediately start a grab again to quickly turn around. In the following section, input a grab when you reach the top of the slope, then cancel it and input a grab slide to get back up to mach 3.

You can also input a long jump instead of a grab slide to grab onto walls behind Peppino. In the following section, perform a mach cancel when you pass the timed gate, then long jump towards the wall.
A turnaround mach cancel can also be performed in mid-air. In the following section, perform a mach cancel when you fall from the platform, then grab to gain back your speed.
You can use a mach cancel to grab a wall behind you in mid-air as well! This is frequently refered to as a corner grab.
